    "description": "The list of the original command line arguments passed to the Python executable. The elements of sys.orig_argv are the arguments to the Python interpreter, while the elements of sys.argv are the arguments to the user’s program. Arguments consumed by the interpreter itself will be present in sys.orig_argv and missing from sys.argv. Added in version 3.10.",
